    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>I have found a bug in Zend_Oauth_Client class on _getSignableParametersAsQueryString method.</p>

<p>Based on OAuth specification (<a href="http://oauth.net/core/1.0/#anchor14">http://oauth.net/core/1.0/#anchor14</a>) only POST parameters with content-type of application/x-www-form-urlencoded should be encoded. Otherwise the authorization string won't be valid.</p>

<p>Here the patch:</p>

<p>Zend_Oauth_Client Line #307</p>

<p>Change</p>

<p>if (!empty($this-&gt;paramsPost)) {</p>

<p>With</p>

<p>if (!empty($this-&gt;paramsPost) &amp;&amp; $this-&gt;enctype !== self::ENC_FORMDATA) {</p>

